INTRODUCTION PAGE 1 Computers are  machines that work with instructions.
A instruction is a sequence of activities amongst latitudes, longitudes,
variables, constants, and so on.

Computer scientist is any person that works doing computer programs to analize
data.

Programming languages are all the possible ways we can use to do the acitivities 
we want to through the machine. Languages have different cualities, contexts,
paragigmns, sintagms, signs, sintaxes, etc.

Computer languages give instructions to the machine, to manage input, process it
and throw output. input could be data, output could be information. Data is raw
information is processed.

With programming languages we can do from the easiest and simple program to big
programs with nice GUI and games with heavy requirements, bots, machine
production automatization in big corporations.

Campo de Acción de la Programación

